- [exhales deeply]

29:28.592 --> 29:35.512
♪

29:35.556 --> 29:37.601
- Floyd?

29:37.645 --> 29:39.342
♪

29:41.823 --> 29:41.997
.

29:42.041 --> 29:44.826
- Patient coming through.
Hemodynamically stable.

29:44.870 --> 29:47.742
Let's get him to bay 10.
- Sinus rhythm's steady.

29:47.786 --> 29:50.745
[dramatic music]

29:50.789 --> 29:54.618
♪

29:54.662 --> 29:57.099
- You coming?
- I'll be right there.

29:57.143 --> 29:58.579
- Floyd?

30:00.059 --> 30:01.756
- I've got this.

30:01.800 --> 30:04.846
♪

30:04.890 --> 30:07.544
[door closes]

30:07.588 --> 30:13.594
♪

30:13.637 --> 30:15.683
So, what, you a punisher now?

30:15.726 --> 30:17.859
Talking to me?

30:17.903 --> 30:19.861
- I didn't do anything.

30:19.905 --> 30:22.298
- Do you know
you could have killed him?

30:22.342 --> 30:24.997
- Sorry, Doc, I don't know
what you're talking about.

30:25.040 --> 30:27.869
- I know you're dosing them
with ketamine.

30:27.913 --> 30:30.872
♪

30:30.916 --> 30:32.874
- Why do you even care
what goes on up here?

30:32.918 --> 30:35.921
- These are my patients.

30:35.964 --> 30:39.185
- You think they're like
your compliant invalids

30:39.228 --> 30:41.883
from downstairs.

30:41.927 --> 30:44.103
These scum scream,

30:44.146 --> 30:46.279
bite, spit.

30:46.322 --> 30:48.107
- Hey, you need more help
you ask the warden,

30:48.150 --> 30:50.805
but you leave the medicine
to us, is that clear?

30:50.849 --> 30:54.156
- You do your job,
and I'll do mine.

30:54.200 --> 30:58.900
And I'm gonna do what it takes
to keep these bastards in line.

30:58.944 --> 31:01.947
♪

31:01.990 --> 31:04.950
[printer whirring]

31:04.993 --> 31:07.300
- Finally, it's working.

31:09.128 --> 31:11.217
[sighs]

31:15.003 --> 31:17.919
Useless technology.

31:17.963 --> 31:20.922
[upbeat music]

31:20.966 --> 31:23.925
♪

31:23.969 --> 31:25.231
You were right.
- What do you mean?

31:25.274 --> 31:27.624
- You were right
from the very start.

31:27.668 --> 31:30.932
The technology got it wrong.
Our test results got it wrong.

31:30.976 --> 31:33.239
Think about it--this whole time
we've been testing

31:33.282 --> 31:34.893
for today's pathogens,

31:34.936 --> 31:37.069
but today's pathogens
are all mutated,

31:37.112 --> 31:40.637
evolved variants
of much older strains.

31:40.681 --> 31:43.640
What those men
were exposed to up there

31:43.684 --> 31:45.947
was a much older strain...

31:45.991 --> 31:48.950
of a very common infection.

31:48.994 --> 31:51.126
- So, even if it were
a 99% match,

31:51.170 --> 31:53.824
our equipment will still read
it as a negative result.

31:53.868 --> 31:55.696
- Exactly.

31:55.739 --> 31:57.263
Their initial symptoms
were telling you

31:57.306 --> 31:59.613
they were suffering
from Naegleriasis.

31:59.656 --> 32:01.920
Our collective wisdom
and experience were telling us

32:01.963 --> 32:03.965
they were suffering
from Naegleriasis.

32:04.009 --> 32:06.098
- And our equipment
could not see it.

32:06.141 --> 32:08.274
- This may be
an ancient strain,

32:08.317 --> 32:10.885
but it's essentially
the same old amoeba.

32:10.929 --> 32:13.932
- Which means today's treatment
should still be effective.

32:13.975 --> 32:16.847
[dramatic music]

32:16.891 --> 32:19.763
- ...I'll do mine,
and I'm gonna do what it takes

32:19.807 --> 32:21.983
to keep these bastards
in line.

32:22.027 --> 32:24.116
- You asked for proof.

32:24.159 --> 32:25.856
So?

32:27.336 --> 32:29.295
- Codie Jeffers is going
to be fired,

32:29.338 --> 32:30.774
effective immediately.

32:30.818 --> 32:32.994
Thank you, Doctor.

32:33.038 --> 32:34.691
This practice ends with her.

32:37.781 --> 32:41.829
- ♪ He had
his father's eyes ♪

32:41.872 --> 32:45.093
♪ And his mother's
point of view ♪

32:45.137 --> 32:48.096
- Grandpa and Grandma
are really late.

32:48.140 --> 32:50.011
They're gonna miss
the whole party.

32:50.055 --> 32:53.319
- ♪ He can see through

32:53.362 --> 32:55.277
- They're not coming.

32:55.321 --> 32:59.151
- ♪ Sometimes
the little things... ♪

32:59.194 --> 33:01.675
- Not tonight, not tomorrow.

33:01.718 --> 33:04.112
- But they have to come.

33:04.156 --> 33:06.985
It's been forever
since we've seen them.

33:07.028 --> 33:11.206
I'm the only one
who even remembers them.

33:11.250 --> 33:14.166
- You know, sweetheart,
Grandma and Grandpa...

33:14.209 --> 33:15.689
♪

33:15.732 --> 33:19.345
They don't really understand
our family.

33:19.388 --> 33:23.697
- Is something wrong
with our family?

33:23.740 --> 33:25.786
- No, no.
God, no.

33:25.829 --> 33:27.962
There's not a thing wrong
with our family.

33:28.006 --> 33:31.052
- Then why don't they want
to see us?

33:31.096 --> 33:34.708
[somber music]

33:34.751 --> 33:36.797
- You know, most families,

33:36.840 --> 33:40.366
